unique_ids = unique(data$Subject_ID)

# 70% for training, 30% for testing
train_ids = sample(unique_ids, size = 0.7 * length(unique_ids))
test_ids = setdiff(unique_ids, train_ids)

# training and testing data sets
train_data = data %>% filter(Subject_ID%in% train_ids)
test_data = data %>% filter(Subject_ID%in% test_ids)
cat("Training patients:", length(train_ids), "\n")
## Training patients: 69
cat("Testing patients:", length(test_ids), "\n")
## Testing patients: 30
# Reshape data to wide format to get columns for sc, m06, m12, m24
train_wide = train_data %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = VISCODE, values_from = -c(Subject_ID, VISCODE, Group))

varname = "lh_Precuneus_GausCurv"  
x1 = paste0(varname, "_sc")
x2 = paste0(varname, "_m06")
x3 = paste0(varname, "_m12")
y  = paste0(varname, "_m24")
formula_str = paste0(y, " ~ ", x1, " + ", x2, " + ", x3)
model = lm(as.formula(formula_str), data = train_wide)

# Coefficients
beta_hat = coef(model)

# test data similarly
test_wide = test_data %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = VISCODE, values_from = -c(Subject_ID, VISCODE, Group))

# Prediction
test_wide[[paste0("pred_", y)]] = predict(model, newdata = test_wide)

# Optional: Evaluate model performance
true_vals = test_wide[[y]]
pred_vals = test_wide[[paste0("pred_", y)]]

# R-squared, correlation
correlation = cor(true_vals, pred_vals, use = "complete.obs")
r_squared = summary(model)$r.squared

cat("Variable:", varname, "\n")
## Variable: lh_Precuneus_GausCurv
cat("Correlation:", correlation, "\n")
## Correlation: 0.8689803
cat("R-squared on training data:", r_squared, "\n")
## R-squared on training data: 0.6801803
all_columns = colnames(train_wide)
var_basenames = unique(gsub("_(sc|m06|m12|m24)", "", all_columns))
var_basenames = var_basenames[var_basenames != "Subject_ID"]

results = data.frame(Variable = character(), Correlation = numeric(), R_squared = numeric())

for (varname in var_basenames) {
  x1 = paste0(varname, "_sc")
  x2 = paste0(varname, "_m06")
  x3 = paste0(varname, "_m12")
  y = paste0(varname, "_m24")
  
  # Check if all required columns are present
  if (all(c(x1, x2, x3, y) %in% colnames(train_wide))) {
    model = lm(as.formula(paste0(y, " ~ ", x1, " + ", x2, " + ", x3)), data = train_wide)
    
    test_wide[[paste0("pred_", y)]] = predict(model, newdata = test_wide)
    
    true_vals = test_wide[[y]]
    pred_vals = test_wide[[paste0("pred_", y)]]
    
    correlation = cor(true_vals, pred_vals, use = "complete.obs")
    r_squared = summary(model)$r.squared
    
    results = rbind(results, data.frame(
      Variable = varname,
      Correlation = correlation,
      R_squared = r_squared
    ))
  }
}

# Collect all columns in test_wide that are predictions
pred_cols = grep("^pred_.*_m24$", colnames(test_wide), value = TRUE)

# true values for comparison
true_cols = grep("^[^pred_].*_m24$", colnames(test_wide), value = TRUE)

# Extract PatientID for identification
patient_ids = test_wide$Subject_ID 

# data frame with predicted and true values
predicted_df = data.frame(Subject_ID = patient_ids)

# all predictions
predicted_df = cbind(predicted_df, test_wide[, pred_cols])

# table contains predicted values and true values
for (i in seq_along(pred_cols)) {
  var_name = gsub("^pred_", "", pred_cols[i])
  true_col = var_name
  if (true_col %in% colnames(test_wide)) {
    predicted_df[[paste0("true_", var_name)]] = test_wide[[true_col]]
  }
}

# Loop over each predicted variable
for (pred_col in pred_cols) {
  var_name = gsub("^pred_", "", pred_col)
  true_col = paste0("true_", var_name)
  
  if (true_col %in% colnames(predicted_df)) {
    plot_data = predicted_df[, c("Subject_ID", pred_col, true_col)]
    colnames(plot_data) = c("Subject_ID", "Predicted", "True")
    
    plot = ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = True, y = Predicted)) +
      geom_point(color = "#2c7fb8", alpha = 0.6) +
      geom_abline(slope = 1, intercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
      labs(title = paste("Predicted vs. True for", var_name),
           x = "True Value (m24)", y = "Predicted Value (m24)") +
      theme_minimal()
    
    print(plot)
  }
}
